<h2 class='donnie-index'>'Donnie Yen Ji-dan is a successful actor, martial artist, choreographer, film director, multiple-time world wushu tournament champion. His parents were an odd couple his father being a newspaper editor and his mother being martial arts master. It was his mother that actually taught and got him started practicing martial arts at a young age. She was named Black Belt magazine's "Kung-Fu Artist of the Year" in 1995. Later on down the line Donnie would soon follow her foot steps and be named "Kung-Fu Artist of the Year" in 2009 also by Black Belt magazine. Over the course of time Donnie has been featured in a number of movies and has studied a wide variety of martial arts. These skills include Tai chi chuan, boxing, kickboxing, Jeet Kune Do, Hapkido, Taekwondo, Karate, Muay Thai, Wrestling, Brazilian Jiu-jitsu, Judo, Wing Chun, and Wushu. Due to Yen's extensive list of martial arts he is credited for contributing to popularizing Wing Chun and having schools opened to study that style. In the 2008 movie named "Ip Man"  Donnie Yen played a grandmaster whos unbeatable style was known as Wing Chun. Fans would also come to love the movie because not only was he a famous Grandmaster, he was also the one who taught the iconic Bruce Lee.   </h2>